OL,3,CWorkers at Tetley Tea factory walk out
OL,4,Cover pay
OL,6,FWorkers at a Tetley Tea factory on
OL,7,FTeesside are continuing to strike.
OL,9,FAlmost 150 GMB members, based at the
OL,10,FEaglescliffe site, voted to walk out
OL,11,Fon Monday 23 September, claiming they
OL,12,Fhave had years of real term pay cuts.
OL,14,FTata Consumer Products, which owns the
OL,15,Fsite, says it believes the offers it
OL,16,Fhas made are fair, and it is
OL,17,Fdisappointed in the decision to strike.
